spirituality service and social change fellowship information session events at stanford spirituality service and social change fellowship information session facebook twitter email print add to calendar spirituality service & social change fellows have a nine week fulltime summer experience working at organizations identified by the haas center staff fellows may work in arenas such as health care education human rights environmental justice hunger and homelessness youth empowerment immigrant rights and affordable housing the fellowship also includes a weekly seminar facilitated by fellowship organizers to discuss readings and work experiences open to stanford undergraduate students only come to the information session to learn more about the fellowship and the application process lunch provided when thursday january 12 2012 12 00 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where circle common room old union 3rd floor map audience students tags other public service sponsor hillel at stanford office for religious life haas center for public service contact 723 1762 religious life stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 298 29823 more info last modified january 17 2012
